    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine domini nostri Iesu Christi dei eterni. <persName
                            key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/9">Lotharius</persName> divina
                        ordinante providentia <rs key="#Emperor/king">imperator</rs> augustus.
                        Dignum est, ut imperialis dignitas servorum dei petitiones effectuosa
                        deliberatione libenter obaudiat atque ad dei famulatum utile prebere studeat
                        solatium. Quapropter omnibus fidelibus sancte dei ecclesie presentibus
                        scilicet et futuris notum facimus, quod pro mercedis nostre augumento cuidam
                            <orgName
                            key="#Rent_in_kind #Fluvial_transport #Decima #Teloneum #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Monasteries #Abbots"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/512"><rs key="#Monasteries">monasterio</rs> in
                            honore sancti Ylarii confessoris</orgName> dei constructo quendam
                            <placeName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Churches #Decima #Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Landed_possessions #Wine #Forests #Hay/fodder #Cereals #Rivers #Mills #Ports #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Fluvial_transport #Markets #Teloneum #Rent_in_kind #Canals #Marshes/lagoons/tombolos"
                                ><geogName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Churches #Decima #Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Landed_possessions #Wine #Forests #Hay/fodder #Cereals #Rivers #Mills #Ports #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Fluvial_transport #Markets #Teloneum #Rent_in_kind #Canals #Marshes/lagoons/tombolos"
                                ref="#estates/556"><rs
                                    key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                    >curticellam</rs> Platanum</geogName></placeName> colactam cum
                            <orgName key="#Churches"><rs key="#Churches">capella</rs> in honore
                            sancti Petri</orgName> constructa et <rs key="#Decima">decimis</rs>
                        quoque ad se pertinentibus et <rs key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie"
                            >massariciis</rs> vel <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terris</rs> seu <rs
                            key="#Wine">vineis</rs> atque <rs key="#Forests">silvis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Hay/fodder">pratis</rs> pascuis <rs key="#Cereals">campis</rs>
                        acervis <rs key="#Rivers">fluminibus</rs> rivis <rs key="#Mills"
                            >molendinis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Ports">portubus</rs>
                        <rs key="#Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters">ripatibus</rs>
                        <rs key="#Fluvial_transport #Markets">negotiis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Teloneum">tholoneis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Rent_in_kind">quarantessimis</rs>, cum omnibus quoque ad ipsum
                        dictum portum vel curticellam pertinentibus, cum suis circundatis lateribus
                        -- hoc est a primo latere <rs key="#Canals #Boundary_settings">canale</rs>,
                        quod dicitur Tergola, percurrens usque in capite de <rs
                            key="#Canals #Boundary_settings">fossa</rs>, que dicitur Vissignone, cum
                            <rs key="#Rivers #Boundary_settings">rivo</rs>, qui dicitur Mauro, ad
                        ipsam fossam pertinente usque in <rs key="#Marshes/lagoons/tombolos"
                            >paludem</rs> et <rs key="#Sea">aquas salsas</rs> percurrente cum <rs
                            key="#Canals #Boundary_settings">fossa</rs>, que dicitur Caparia, cum
                        suis rivis ad se pertinentibus usque ipsum terminum habente et a latere <rs
                            key="#Shores #Boundary_settings">argerem</rs> capite firmante in
                        flumine, quod dicitur Vne, usque in paludem et aquas salsas percurrente, et
                        latera in predicta curticella Pladano nomine persistunt -- nostra
                        munificentia perhenniter possidendam in eiusdem sancti loci contulimus
                        utilitatem. Unde pro firmitatis gratia presentem auctoritatem nostram eidem
                        venerabili <rs key="#Bishops">abbati</rs> nomine <persName key="#Abbots"
                            ref="#people/669">Deusdedit</persName> fieri iussimus, per quam
                        precipientes precipimus, ut ab hinc in futurum iure firmissimo pars ipsius
                        monasterii easdem res quieto ordine teneat atque absque cuiuspiam
                        contrarietate aut inquietudine possideat et faciat exinde quicquid
                        utilitatis dicto monasterio placuerit. Hec vero auctoritas, ut pleniorem in
                        dei nomine habeat vigorem et pro futuro tempore inconvulsam obtineat
                        firmitatem, manu nostra propria subter firmavimus et anuli nostri
                        impressione adsignari iussimus. Signum (M.) Lotharii piissimi augusti. Data
                        VIII idus maii anno Christo propicio imperii domni Lotharii gloriosissimi
                        augusti decimo octavo, indictione II; actum <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Function #Residential #Palatium"
                            ref="#places/65">Papie</placeName> in <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Function #Residential #Palatium"
                            >palatio regio</rs>; in dei nomine feliciter amen. </ab>
                </div>
